S&P Reiterates Warning of 50% Chance of U.S. Downgrade Within Three Months

-- B y   D a v e   L i e d t k a
-- 
2011-07-21T14:35:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/s-p-reiterates-warning-of-50-chance-of-u-s-downgrade-within-three-months.html
Standard & Poor’s  reiterated that
there is a 50 percent chance that it will lower the U.S. credit
rating within three months as lawmakers struggle to reach
agreement over raising the nation’s debt ceiling and deficit
reduction.  S&P  said  on July 14 there was a one-in-two possibility that
it would cut the U.S. AAA by one or more levels if the
government hasn’t agreed on a “credible solution” on the
nation’s debt level. The company reiterated the warning in a
report today outlining three hypothetical scenarios.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dave Liedtka at   dliedtka@bloomberg.net  